narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A great course for general understanding of music theory. I would suggest that anyone who wants to deepen their understanding of music, even if they don't plan on taking any higher level courses, to take this class.
I absolutely loved this class! Would highly recommend for those very interested in music and/or composition, & if you can, definitely take with Quinn.
This is an amazing course. Take it with Ian Quinn if possible!

I think that the course had a fairly steep learning curve, but this was fairly advertised to prospective students, and the frequent quizzes for the first part of the class greatly helped in the latter part. I would definitely recommend the course to anyone who wants to deepen their understanding of tonal music.

Music major prerequisites aside, I would definitely recommend this course to another student who is interested in gaining a much deeper understanding of music theory than they previously had. Overall, this course was an interesting, thorough introduction to many aspects of music theory that go beyond that of a high school theory course. I would further recommend this to any student interested in learning to write music, though I would advise them that it is not an instruction in writing per se.
